[?2004l[?2004h>    - This caused almost all data to be reprocessed on resume
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. INSERT OR REPLACE overwrote existing aggregates instead of accumulating
[?2004l[?2004h>    - On resume, previous batch results were lost/replaced
[?2004l[?2004h>    - This caused data loss for categories already processed
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. Checkpoint file not properly flushed to disk
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Used open() without context manager
[?2004l[?2004h>    - No explicit flush() or fsync() calls
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Could result in empty/corrupt checkpoint on crash
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> Fixes Applied:
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. Changed checkpoint to save actual line number (start_from + lines_processed)
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Now correctly skips all previously processed lines
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Added lines_processed counter to track position
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. Changed to INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE
[?2004l[?2004h>    - Accumulates total_value and count instead of replacing
